postcontent: Just wanted to get some feedback from those who've upgraded their stock M&P triggers to Apex triggers.  I love my M&P's (9c & .40c) for various reasons not the least of which is that I have relatively smallish hands and the M&P grip fits perfectly.  But the stock trigger on these things are garbage and I've spent the better part of 2 years attempting to ignore it.  I know a lot of folks replace the triggers with Apex but I was wondering if it really made that much of a difference.  I mean, am I paying $125 for something that'll turn my M&P into a superb handling PPQ clone, or is it just a slight upgrade to the steaming pile of crap the M&P stock trigger is?  The price tag of the Apex system doesn't bother me as it's a small price to pay relative to cost and hassle of dumping these firearms and once again trying to find a more suitable fit.  Feedback?
